<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,652,784]" pageId="20" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,652,677]" pageId="20" pageNumber="31">Remarks.</emphasis>
The publication date of the genus name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Michaelsen" authorityYear="1936" box="[724,867,652,677]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossoscolecidae" genus="Martiodrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="20" pageNumber="31" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[724,867,652,677]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="31">Martiodrilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is somewhat controversial. In several publications and databases (
<emphasis box="[324,357,689,712]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="31">e.g</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation box="[372,508,688,712]" pageId="20" pageNumber="31" refId="ref13651" refString="James, S. W. (1990) Diplotrema murchiei and D. papillata, new earthworms (Oligochaeta: Megascolecidae) from Mexico. Acta Zoologica Mexicana, 38, 18 - 27." type="journal article">James 1990</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation box="[520,579,688,712]" pageId="20" pageNumber="31" refId="ref13687" refString="James, S. W. &amp; Davidson, S. (2012) Molecular phylogeny of earthworms (Annelida: Crassiclitellata) based on 28 S, 18 S and 16 S gene sequences. Invertebrate Systematics, 26, 213 - 229. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / IS 11012" type="journal article">2012</bibRefCitation>
, 
<collectionCode box="[591,645,688,712]" pageId="20" pageNumber="31">ITIS</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode box="[658,723,688,712]" pageId="20" pageNumber="31">GIBF</collectionCode>
) it is written as 1937, however on the journal's website (http:// onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1469-7998.1936.tb06306.x/abstract) it is clearly stated that the paper was published in December, 1936.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
